channel.title: CVE Feed for Dell -- RSA Archer
channel.description: The latest CVEs for Dell -- RSA Archer

item.title: CVE-2019-3756|2024-09-16T17:39:15.211Z -- dell -- rsa%20archer
item.description: RSA Archer, versions prior to 6.6 P3 (6.6.0.3), contain an information disclosure vulnerability. Information relating to the backend database gets disclosed to low-privileged RSA Archer users' UI under certain error conditions.

item.title: CVE-2019-3715|2024-09-16T18:43:54.780Z -- dell -- rsa%20archer
item.description: RSA Archer versions, prior to 6.5 SP1, contain an information exposure vulnerability. Users' session information is logged in plain text in the RSA Archer log files. An authenticated malicious local user with access to the log files may obtain the exposed information to use it in further attacks.

item.title: CVE-2020-5334|2024-09-16T18:59:21.546Z -- dell -- rsa%20archer
item.description: RSA Archer, versions prior to 6.7 P2 (6.7.0.2), contains a Document Object Model (DOM) based cross-site scripting vulnerability. A remote unauthenticated attacker could potentially exploit this vulnerability by tricking a victim application user to supply malicious HTML or JavaScript code to DOM environment in the browser. The malicious code is then executed by the web browser in the context of the vulnerable web application.

item.title: CVE-2019-3758|2024-09-16T17:08:48.274Z -- dell -- rsa%20archer
item.description: RSA Archer, versions prior to 6.6 P2 (6.6.0.2), contain an improper authentication vulnerability. The vulnerability allows sysadmins to create user accounts with insufficient credentials. Unauthenticated attackers could gain unauthorized access to the system using those accounts.

item.title: CVE-2020-5333|2024-09-16T16:43:48.571Z -- dell -- rsa%20archer
item.description: RSA Archer, versions prior to 6.7 P3 (6.7.0.3), contain an authorization bypass vulnerability in the REST API. A remote authenticated malicious Archer user could potentially exploit this vulnerability to view unauthorized information.
